title: For Sale:  Mossberg 12 Field package
postcontent: Mossberg 12 gauge, five rounds through it you can still see factory oil and smell it, very clean shotgun. My first Mossberg Maverick 88, good ol Mossberg just a Mossberg 500 with a crossbolt saftey in case you aren't familiar with these.A Maxpedition satchel style bag, the slightly smaller version of the "fatboy" not too big or small you can throw in a couple boxes of shells of loose ammo and still have room for a couple of snacks on the bottom easily. Plus a bottle of water in the side tension pouch. If you look at the pictures it also has a CCW pouch so it can pull double duty if you're into that.   Fifteen rounds of Military Grade 00 Buckshot, six three inch Magnum slugs, a nice clump of OD Green paracord I keep in the bag, and a KaBar Mark 1 Navy knife on the strap of the satchel, I polished the blade with mothers myself. The knife is well taken care of sharpened and oiled, only some minor dings on the base of the pommel from setting in some tent stakes.  All in all a nice little package ready to go out into the field, take deer rabbit or whatever with a nice blade on a nice pack too. 300

title: For Sale:  ***LOOK*** THE LEGEND, BLACK TALON 45 ACP 230 GRAIN
postcontent: I have several pristine boxes of New Old Stock Winchester Black Talon 45 ACP 230 grain hollow points. This is the holy grail of ammo collecting, extremely rare and hard to find in any condition, nearly impossible to find this nice. These are the original, mythological "Teflon coated bullets", which went out of production in 1993 and will never be made again. Black Talon ammunition continues to skyrocket in value, commonly selling for over $100 a box online, when you can find it. Here is your chance to own the legend, the most sought after rare ammo you can legally buy and possibly the nastiest hollowpoint ever made. I am interested in trade or cash offers. Trades considered are guns, knives, 45/357/12gauge ammo, or electronics or other guy stuff. Hesitant to let this ammo go, just figured Id put some lines out and see what kind of offers I get.
